climbs.name: Snow Flake Right
climbs.fa: FA 2015 Belyn Grant, Ney Grant and Betsy Grant

content.description: Mantle up onto the ledge, then undercling the flake all the way around to the right and up the face. It is conceivable that the bottom left portion of the flake could break off, so be careful in pulling out on it.
content.protection: TR on two bolt ring anchor
content.location: Big flake on wall is Snowflake

climbs.name: Snow Flake Left
climbs.fa: FA 2015 Belyn Grant, Ney Grant and Betsy Grant

content.description: This is a tightly bolted fun sport climb (4 bolts) or top roped. Mantle up onto the ledge to clip the first bolt. It is conceivable that the bottom left portion of the flake could break off when doing the mantel move, so pull down not out. Once on the ledge moving up doesn't involve pulling on the flake.
content.location: Large flake on wall is snowflake.

climbs.name: September Flake
climbs.fa: FA 2015 Belyn Grant, Ney Grant and Betsy Grant

content.description: This is a fun flake that turns into a crack higher up.
content.protection: Small / Medium cams or an easy top rope.

climbs.name: Ides of Fall
climbs.fa: FA 2015 Belyn Grant, Ney Grant and Betsy Grant

content.description: The left-most climb is an undercling that starts at ground level. The granite surface is a bit loose and it may not get climbed enough to get clean so be careful. Start off the ground in an undercling and move left and transition into a lieback.
content.location: Left most, almost around the corner from other climbs.

climbs.name: Autumnal Cracks
climbs.fa: FA 2015 Belyn Grant, Ney Grant and Betsy Grant

content.description: Two hand cracks start up the wall. Using both cracks it is easy 5.7 but you can choose to induce much more pain to your hands and feet by using only one crack or the other. The rock is quite rough so bring tape if you want to practice jams.
content.protection: Small / Medium cams or top rope.
